<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 24 at 7:01PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Patchy Freezing Drizzle and Locally Slippery Travel Possible
Overnight...
Across portions of the southern Adirondacks, upper Hudson Valley
and southern Vermont, patchy freezing drizzle will remain
possible overnight as temperatures remain around the freezing
mark. This may lead to locally slippery travel conditions on
untreated ground surfaces overnight, especially across higher
terrain areas.
Motorists and pedestrians should remain vigilant for possible
slippery ground conditions overnight, including on less traveled
roadways, driveways and parking lots.</description>
